Migrant herders searching for pasture and water are to blame for rising crime in Laikipia county, Devolution and National Planning CS Mwangi Kiunjuri has said.The former Laikipia East MP said the herdsmen are invading residents&rsquo; farms and even stealing their livestock.He urged the pastoralists should respect other people&rsquo;s property and obey the law to ensure peace.Once the rains begin, the herders should leave Laikipia, the CS said.He spoke on Saturday at Olmoran trading centre in Laikipia.Kiunjuri said the government had promised to deploy police reservists to improve security.&ldquo;All villages in the bandit-prone areas will be provided with five NPRs with the aim of boosting security,&rdquo; he said.